# Capy-POS Development Rules

## 📋 Definition of Done (DoD)

A ticket/story is **NOT considered done** until ALL of the following criteria are met:

### 1. Implementation Complete
- [ ] All acceptance criteria from the Business Analyst are satisfied
- [ ] Code follows Clean Architecture boundaries (Domain → Application → Infrastructure → Presentation)
- [ ] TypeScript strict mode compliance (no `any` types)
- [ ] Angular patterns followed (standalone components, OnPush, Signals)

### 2. Testing Complete
- [ ] Unit tests pass with **≥ 80% coverage** on new/modified code
- [ ] E2E tests pass for affected user flows
- [ ] Tests are fast, isolated, and deterministic
- [ ] Edge cases are covered

### 3. Pull Request Created
- [ ] Feature branch pushed to remote (`git push origin feature/[branch-name]`)
- [ ] PR created with clear title: `[Ticket-ID] Feature description`
- [ ] PR body includes: Summary, Acceptance Criteria, Testing checklist
- [ ] PR is linked to the ticket/story

### 4. PR Reviewed and Approved by BOTH:
- [ ] **🏛️ Architect** — Architectural review (layer compliance, dependency direction, system impact, no cross-agent coupling)
- [ ] **👨‍💻 Tech Lead** — Technical review (code quality, TypeScript conventions, Angular patterns, test coverage, implementation correctness)

> ⚠️ **MANDATORY**: Both the Architect AND Tech Lead must approve the PR before it can be merged. No exceptions. If either requests changes, those must be addressed before re-review.

### 5. Merge & Cleanup
- [ ] All BLOCKER comments resolved
- [ ] PR merged to main branch
- [ ] Feature branch deleted after merge

---

## 🔄 Workflow Rules

### Planning Phase
When starting any new ticket/feature, consult these agents in order:
1. **Product Owner** → Confirm story and priority
2. **Architect** → Validate technical feasibility, assess architectural impact
3. **Tech Lead** → Estimate complexity, define implementation strategy and testing approach
4. **Business Analyst** → Confirm acceptance criteria
5. **UX Lead** → Confirm design specs (if UI work)
6. **DBA** → Confirm data requirements (if data work)

### Building Phase
1. Create a feature branch: `git checkout -b feature/[ticket-id]-[short-description]`
2. **Update GitHub issue status to "In Progress"** using `gh issue edit [issue-number] --add-label "in-progress"`
3. Follow TDD: Red → Green → Refactor
4. Commit frequently with meaningful messages
5. Keep PRs focused and small (< 400 lines when possible)

### Reviewing Phase (Definition of Done Gate)
1. Push branch and create PR
2. **Update GitHub issue status to "In Review"** using `gh issue edit [issue-number] --add-label "in-review" --remove-label "in-progress"`
3. Request review from **Architect** (architectural compliance)
4. Request review from **Tech Lead** (technical quality)
5. Address any feedback/changes requested
6. Once BOTH approve → **Update issue to "Ready to Merge"** using `gh issue edit [issue-number] --add-label "ready-to-merge" --remove-label "in-review"`

### Shipping Phase (Post-Approval, Pre-Merge)

> ⚠️ **MANDATORY**: After both reviews are approved, execute ALL of the following in parallel before closing the ticket:

**Run these agent consultations in parallel:**

| Agent | Responsibility | Output |
|-------|---------------|--------|
| **Scrum Master** | Update sprint board, velocity, burndown | Sprint status update in memory |
| **QA Tester** | Verify acceptance criteria met, confirm test coverage | QA sign-off comment on PR |
| **Code Reviewer** | Final code quality check, patterns review | Code review comment on PR |
| **UX Lead** | Verify UI matches design specs (if UI work) | UX sign-off |
| **Marketing** | Write release notes for the feature | Release notes in PR description |

**Evidence & Demo (REQUIRED):**
- [ ] **Capture a demo** of the feature working using Playwright MCP browser or E2E test
- [ ] Save screenshot/evidence to `evidence/S[sprint]-[story]-[description].png`
- [ ] **Attach evidence to the PR** as a comment: `gh pr comment [pr-number] --body "## Demo\n![evidence](evidence/...)"` 
- [ ] If E2E test exists, run it and attach results
- [ ] If no E2E test exists, capture manual demo via Playwright browser

**Board & Issue Management:**
1. Merge PR to main: `gh pr merge [pr-number] --squash --delete-branch`
2. Close the issue: `gh issue close [issue-number] --comment "✅ Completed in PR #[pr-number]. Demo attached."`
3. Update knowledge graph memory with completion status
4. Update PROJECT_STATUS.md with sprint progress

---

## 🚫 Anti-Patterns to Avoid
- Never merge without Architect + Tech Lead approval
- Never skip tests to "ship faster"
- Never put domain logic in components or infrastructure
- Never use `any` type — use generics, unknown, or proper typing
- Never create circular dependencies between agents/modules
- **Never skip moving the card across the board** — issue labels MUST be updated at EVERY phase transition (see below)
- Never skip consulting the **fullstack-dev** agent during the Building phase
- Never use long PR descriptions — PR `--body` must be ≤ 200 characters

---

## 📐 Code Standards Quick Reference
- Max 300 lines per file
- Standalone components only (no NgModules for new code)
- OnPush change detection everywhere
- Signals for state, computed for derived state
- inject() function over constructor injection
- Barrel exports (index.ts) for public APIs
- Feature-based folder structure

---

## 🎯 GitHub Issue Status Tracking

**MANDATORY**: Update GitHub issue status at each phase transition:

| Phase Transition | Command | Labels |
|-----------------|---------|--------|
| Start work | `gh issue edit [#] --add-label "in-progress"` | `in-progress` |
| Create PR | `gh issue edit [#] --add-label "in-review" --remove-label "in-progress"` | `in-review` |
| Both reviews approved | `gh issue edit [#] --add-label "ready-to-merge" --remove-label "in-review"` | `ready-to-merge` |
| After merge | `gh issue close [#] --comment "Completed in PR #[pr-number]"` | closed |

> 💡 **Tip**: Always update the issue status to keep the project board in sync with actual progress.

---

## 🤖 Agent Consultation Reference

| Phase | Agents to Consult |
|-------|-------------------|
| Planning | product-owner → architect → tech-lead → business-analyst → ux-lead → scrum-master → dba |
| Building | fullstack-dev → qa-tester → devops |
| Reviewing (PR) | architect (REQUIRED) → tech-lead (REQUIRED) → code-reviewer → qa-tester → product-owner |
| Shipping | devops → marketing → scrum-master |
